rComments: Very kind Professor! I also found his  lecture notes  very useful and organized, I saved them for future 4th year courses :D

Professor Westwood is very a very kind man. His tests are hard and the content is hard but he does help you if you need it. Lectures were a little boring as his tone of voice is dull but the material itself was very interesting.  He is very sweet however, and he listens to students if they have any concerns. He is a loveable person
Nice professor.  Speaks really lowly, on the verge of mumbling.  Although he does know his stuff really well
Nice professors.  Speaks really lowly, on the verge of mumbling.  Knows his stuff!
Prof. Westwood is great as a prof - explains stuff really well and really nice person!

I loved the course. The first part on gene expression was a bit dull and definitely review for most students. The cancer part of the course was really interesting. I highly recommend reading the text for the cancer part. Overall as an individual Prof Westwood is very nice and helpful and kinda cute :)
Tests on what he teaches.  Goes out of his way to clearly summarize difficult material.  Very helpful and easy to approach.
